OL,3,C'We need to relieve suffering' -
OL,4,Creaction in South West to assisted
OL,5,Cdying vote
OL,7,FDr Perry does think that patients
OL,8,Fdeserve the right to choose, however,
OL,9,Fshe says that choice is not genuine if
OL,10,Fa patient does not have access to
OL,11,Fsufficient palliative care.
OL,13,FDr Perry explained: "For a patient in
OL,14,Fhospital, they might be offered
OL,15,Fassisted dying, or assisted suicide,
OL,16,Fby many doctors over many times.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
