OL,3,C'We need to relieve suffering' -
OL,4,Creaction in South West to assisted
OL,5,Cdying vote
OL,7,F"I feel that is coercive, and that
OL,8,Ftroubles me. And because of the doctor-
OL,9,Fpatient relationship they will think
OL,10,F'maybe I should die, maybe they know
OL,11,Fwhat's best for me.'
OL,13,F"They might then start considering
OL,14,Fassisted dying, when they might never
OL,15,Fhave considered it before."
OL,17,FDr Perry believes assisted dying will
OL,18,Fhave irreversible consequences, and is
OL,19,Fconcerned about the impact it will
OL,20,Fhave on the elderly and vulnerable.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
